  "text": "Answering this question is important because the use of a species for one purpose may increase the chances that it will be tried and harvested for another purpose. For example, in a compilation of studies from the northern region of South America, [CITATION_1] suggest that most medicinal plants have been adopted because of their value as food or medicine. Thus, plants used as ornamental and food products would be more likely to be incorporated into local pharmacopoeias (see an implication of this idea in the hypothesis of versatility - [CITATION_2] .",
